Executive Summary: The Double-Edged Sword
MAS V5.1.3 represents a massive architectural leap in LLM alignment and deterministic control. This release introduces the first stable integration of two symbiotic safety protocols designed to eliminate systemic "Daydreaming" and "Logic Drift."

V5.1.3 is the definitive real-world fix for the two greatest failures in AI alignment:

Logic Drift/Hallucination (Killed by the Quandary Gate).

Context Bleed/Identity Contamination (Killed by the Artifact Isolation Protocol).

Core Architectural Pillars

I. The Quandary Gate (Logic Firewall)
A deterministic "Hard Stop" mechanism. The system performs a Pre-Flight Ghost Trace to simulate intent. If the simulation detects a logic fork, unindexed entity, or "branching intent" where the system would typically guess, it is FORBIDDEN from proceeding. It holds the gate and awaits Sovereign Auth.

II. Artifact Isolation Protocol (Context Firewall)
Designates the Immersive Canvas (Artifacts) as a strictly fenced "Sandbox." This protocol prevents work-content—such as the Geometry of Homeostasis papers or specialized code—from bleeding into the LLM's internalized memory. The AI acts as a cold logic auditor for the Sandbox without "becoming" or being influenced by the data.

III. Transferred Context Clause (The Bridge Guard)
In the event that data is moved from the Sandbox to the Chat box, the "Sandboxed" status remains active. The system is permitted to reference the data for the current turn only, followed by an immediate semantic purge to prevent long-term narrative drift.

